      "detail": "Disclaimed risk means the aggregator accepts no liability for competitive harm that aggregate products create for individual data producers. Data producers bear the risk that their mandated-open data is aggregated into products that compete with their own market position. The risk asymmetry mirrors the value asymmetry of the aggregation paradox. Disclaimed risk demonstrates the complete absence of reciprocity in the aggregation relationship."
