      "detail": "Ecosystem lock-in means customers have invested in tools, integrations, and workflows that depend on the platform's specific aggregate products. Switching would require replacing not just the data source but the entire analytical infrastructure built around it. The lock-in extends beyond data access to the complete analytical ecosystem the aggregator has created. Ecosystem lock-in is the market-power expression of how aggregation converts regulated openness into commercial dependency."
